<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-31T10:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-31T10:44:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/555: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-31T15:00:00-00:44">March 31,
                                    1942—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>113. From McBride. Agreement signed today.<note n="21" xml:id="d451fn21">For text, see Department of State Executive Agreement Series No.
                                275, or 56 Stat. (pt. 2) 1621.</note> Am departing tonight on TWA
                            stratoliner for Washington.</p>
                        <p>Department’s 75, March 29, 4 p.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d451fn22">Not
                                printed.</note> President Barclay consents to RAF refueling at
                            Fisherman Lake on following conditions:</p>
                        <p>That planes refuel only and take off as soon as possible, crews to wear
                            civilian clothes, consent granted temporarily until airports in Liberia
                            can be defended by American forces. Colonel Kemp at Accra informed.
                            [McBride.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>